document_data.Usages:
[[File:Flax Fiber.png|thumb|200px|''A sample of flax fibers.'']]
* The seeds of this plant could be pressed into a versatile substance known as [[linseed oil]].
* The fibers of this plant were commonly cultivated for use in textiles in both Faerûn as well as string used for everyday purposes and those used with [[bow]]s and [[crossbow]]s. The inner fiber of the flax plant was separated and spun into [[yarn]], woven into fabric and bleached.{{Cite dungeon/133/The Möbius Scrolls|98}} Most homes had a small hand-, backstrap-, or wall-[[loom]]s that they used to make homespun linen and other textiles.{{Cite web/theedverse/2020-05-16 - Homespun Cloth}}
* [[Shimmerweave]] was made by a particular process involving oiled flax.{{Cite archive/Greenwood's Grotto/2023-05-01/Shimmerweave}}
* In [[Evermeet]], [[gold elf]] [[wizard]]s often wore sashes made from flax fibers that were woven into an intricate knotwork.
* [[Torch]]es commonly used flax soaked in [[tallow]] as the fuel source.
* On the [[Malatran Plateau]], wizards used flax seeds as a [[material component]] for the ''[[Enlarge/reduce|Enlarge]]'' [[spell]].<ref>{{Cite web/RPGA Living Jungle/Jungle Tales 7}}
* Wood elves made linen from wild flax they gathered.
